{
  "texts": [
    "For training, we used the AdamW optimizer with betas of (0.9, 0.95), a weight decay of 0.1, and an epsilon of 1e-8.",
    "The learning rate started at zero and warmed up linearly over 10 epochs to 1e-4 before decaying tenfold according to a cosine annealing schedule.",
    "We used a gradient accumulation of 32 to simulate a larger batch size.",
    "Each training stage consisted of 100 epochs using mixed precision training and gradient clipping to a Euclidean norm of 1.0.",
    "For contrastive learning, we used standard hyperparameters 56, 57."
  ]
}